  "text_preview": "\"light\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► American Sign Language: \"light\" The concept of \"light\" has many meanings. There are many ways to sign \"light.\" \"LIGHTS\" or \"LIGHTS-ON\" This version of light is used to refer to \"overhead lighting.\" Question: \"Why do Deaf tend to hang out in the kitchen?\" Answer: \"Good lighting.\" If you use a \"double motion\" with this sign it means \"FLASH the LIGHTS.\" Flashing the lights is a method of quickly getting the attention of a whole group of people. Sample sentence: Why does the teacher flash the lights off and on? = TEACHER FLASH-LIGHTS, WHY? The answer to this question is \"So that the students will look up and pay attention.\" Getting attention this way should only be done by people familiar with Deaf C"
}
